BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shareholders of Walt Disney Co. filed a class-action lawsuit charging that 
company directors breached their fiduciary duty by adopting a "poison pill" 
anti-takeover plan in June . . . Hitachi Ltd. has dropped a patent infringement 
suit filed in May against U.S. electronics firm Motorola Inc. . . . Los 
Angeles-based Angeles Corp. said it agreed to sell its Quinoco oil and gas 
businesses to Saxon Oil Development Partners, Dallas, for $26.5 million . . . 
Restaurant chain TGI Friday's will become a private company in a merger with 
Carlson Hospitality Group Inc. of Minnesota, parent of the Radisson hotel chain 
. . . A U.S. Bankruptcy Court judge approved the appointment of an independent 
examiner to study alleged fraud at Phoenix, Ariz.-based American Continental 
Corp., a real estate and savings and loan holding company. 
</P>
