<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the second attack on his home in two months, a man found his house defaced 
in the latest in a series of attacks on gays by assailants espousing hatred of 
homosexuals, San Francisco police said. Glen Eichelberger awoke on his 44th 
birthday to find anti-gay epithets painted on the stucco wall of his Sunset 
District house. The vandals also splashed Eichelberger's car with red paint. 
"This is terrorism," Eichelberger said. Also scrawled on the wall were the 
letters "SDI," which police say stands for Sunset District Inc., a gang of 
white youths espousing a white-power philosophy that includes hatred of Jews 
and homosexuals, among others. Eichelberger's home was attacked about two 
months ago by vandals who stole a gay pride flag and returned it half burned 
with black swastikas and anti-gay slogans written on it, police said. 
Eichelberger speculated that his work volunteering for AIDS victims may have 
motivated the vandals' action. Police said they have stepped up patrols in the 
area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
VANDALISM; HOMOSEXUALS; HARASSMENT; SUNSET DISTRICT INC (GANG); HATE CRIMES; 
GANGS -- SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
