<P>
The supporters and opponents of Folsom's slow-growth initiative agree that the 
city needs a second traffic bridge over the American River. But they cannot 
agree where the bridge should be built. And the two sides are far apart in 
their interpretation of what Measure N, to be on the ballot Aug. 22, says about 
a second bridge for Folsom. Proponents said the initiative requires the city to 
study the possibility of building the bridge just below Folsom Dam. A "yes" 
vote also will prohibit the building of a bridge over Oak Avenue Parkway or 
other areas leading into residential streets. Opponents say the measure is 
confusing. Some believe that it mandates a bridge below the dam while others 
say the language in the initiative is so unclear that lawyers will be working 
overtime to interpret it. 
