<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
XEROX POSTS 7% PROFIT INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STAMFORD, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xerox Corp. reported a 7% increase in second quarter profits today, saying the 
results indicate it is on track toward achieving its goals in a major 
restructuring launched in January. 
</P>
<P>
The office products company said profits rose to $179 million, or $1.67 a 
share, from $167 million, or $1.59 a share, in the year-ago second quarter. 
Revenues rose 7% to $4.4 billion. 
</P>
<P>
In January Xerox set a major restructuring program, including layoffs of 2,000, 
or 2% of its work force, and an exit from the medical systems business. It took 
a pretax charge of $275 million to write off the non-performing assets. 
</P>
