<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
NOVACEK WINS HILVERSUM TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HILVERSUM, Netherlands 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karel Novacek of Czechoslovakia defeated Emilio Sanchez of Spain 6-2, 6-4 today 
to capture the Hilversum tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The eighth-seeded Novacek needed one hour, 10 minutes to oust Sanchez, who was 
seeded second, in a match that had been scheduled for Sunday but was postponed 
because of persistent rain at the Melkhuisje tennis complex. 
</P>
<P>
Novacek, ranked 88th on the world computer listing, collected $14,000 for the 
victory. 
</P>
